DMOZ About Become an Editor Suggest a Site Help Login Share via Facebook Share via Twitter Share via LinkedIn Share via e-Mail Visit DMOZ on Facebook Visit DMOZ on Twitter the entire directory Regional North America Help with Search Regional North America 552,535 The continent of North America was formed from the primordial continent of Laurentia, and is the third largest continent in the world with a land area of 24.3 million sq km. It encompasses all lands and nearby islands between the Isthmus of Panama and the North Pole, inclusive, in the Western Hemisphere. The ODP defines North America as Bermuda, Canada, Greenland (Kalaalit Nunaat), Mexico, Saint Pierre and Miquelon, and the United States of America. Related categories including other North American nations are Regional/Caribbean and Regional/Central_America/. Please submit sites only to the most relevant category. Subcategories 24 Bermuda 134 Canada 64,656 Greenland 86 Mexico 2,047 Saint Pierre and Miquelon 11 United States 485,299 Regions 100 Arts and Entertainment 5 Business and Economy 86 Education 2 Employment 3 Government 2 Guides and Directories 1 Health 1 Maps and Views 4 News and Media 0 Real Estate 26 Recreation and Sports 5 Science and Environment 4 Shopping 9 Society and Culture 24 Transportation 3 Travel and Tourism 65 Weather 0 Related categories 2 Regional Caribbean 3,969 Regional Central America 2,654 Category editors: jazz william13 cherel Last update: March 8, 2017 at 1:04:07 UTC Regional Science Shopping Society Sports All Languages Arts Business Computers Games Health Home News Recreation Reference "Regional North America" search on: AOL - Ask - Bing - DuckDuckGo - Gigablast - Google - ixquick - Yahoo - Yandex - Yippy Copyright Â© 1998-2017 AOL Inc. Terms of Use Built by CMBuild